				<h3><strong>Schools4All 2012 Promotion</strong></h3>
<p> <strong>Official Rules</strong></p>
<p> <strong>NO PURCHASE NECESSARY</strong></p>
<p><strong>PROMOTION DESCRIPTION:</strong> The Schools4All 2012 Promotion (the “<strong>Promotion</strong>”) is a fundraising challenge that begins on or about November 30, 2012 at 12:01 a.m. Eastern Time (“<strong>ET</strong>”) and ends on February 28, 2013 at 11:59 p.m. ET (the “<strong>Promotion Period</strong>”). The Promotion consists of nine (9) weekly drawings (the “<strong>Drawings</strong>”) to award eighteen (18) weekly prizes (each, a “<strong>Weekly Prize</strong>”) and a fundraising sweepstakes to award the “Grand Prize”, “First Prize”, “Second Prize”, “Third Prize” and “Mobile Prize” as more fully described below.  Weekly Prizes will be awarded at the end of each of the “Weekly Periods” as defined below. Participation in the Promotion does not constitute entry and/or participation in any other promotion, contest or sweepstakes. By participating in the Promotion, each participant unconditionally accepts and agrees to comply with and abide by these Official Rules and the decisions of Pencils of Promise, Inc., 37 West 28th Street, 3rd Floor, New York, NY 10001 (“<strong>Sponsor</strong>”), which shall be final and binding in all respects.</p>

            

<p><strong>ELIGIBILITY:</strong> Only legal residents of the United States who are thirteen (13) years of age or older are eligible to enter. Participants who are under the legal age of majority in their state or province of primary residence (a “<strong>minor</strong>”) must get their parent or legal guardian’s permission to participate in the Promotion.  Minor participants will be required to provide parental consent in a form satisfactory to the Sponsor before he or she can be declared a winner and any prize can be awarded.  Sponsor, Scooter Braun Projects, Bieber Time Touring, Justin Bieber, Scott “Scooter” Braun, Island Def Jam, RBMG Music Group, Schoolboy Records, Barnes & Noble, and each of their respective parents, subsidiaries, affiliates, distributors, retailers, sales representatives, advertising and promotion agencies and each of their respective officers, directors and employees (collectively, the “<strong>Promotion Entities</strong>”) and the immediate family members, and/or those living in the same household of each, are ineligible to enter the Promotion or win a prize.</p>

            

<p><strong>HOW IT WORKS:</strong> To enter the Promotion, visit the web site, <a href="http://www.schools4all.org" title="Schools4All" target="new">http://www.schools4all.org</a> (the “<strong>Website</strong>”) and complete the required information to create your fundraising page (“<strong>Fundraising Page</strong>”). Once you have created the Fundraising Page, you can begin collecting donations directly at the Fundraising Page.  All Fundraising Pages must be linked to a recognized school in the United States as more fully described at the Website.  If you are currently not enrolled in any of the recognized schools listed at the Website, you must select a school from the list to be associated with.  A school page will be created for each school selected that will accumulate the total amount donated on each Fundraising Page associated with that school (the “<strong>School Fundraising Page</strong>”). The following prizes are available through this Promotion:
<br /><br />
To be eligible for the Grand Prize, the School Fundraising Page must have a balance of at least $25.  For every $25 that the School Fundraising Page accumulates during the Promotion Period, it will receive one (1) entry into the Grand Prize drawing.  There is no limit to an eligible school’s potential number of entries in the Grand Prize drawing.  At the end of the Promotion Period, all eligible entries will be entered into a random draw sweepstakes to determine the Grand Prize winner.
<br /><br />
To be eligible for the Mobile Prize, from your wireless phone, text the word “FLY” or “FLIGHT” to the short code 877877  (the “<strong>Short Code</strong>”). Once enrolled, you must refer at least five (5) additional subscribers to be eligible for the Mobile Prize.  All eligible participants for this portion of the Promotion will be entered into a random draw sweepstakes to determine the Mobile Prize winner.
<br /><br />
You may receive several text messages in response, including a message confirming your entry, legal disclaimers and options to receive future promotional text messages from Sponsor. You may opt-out of receiving future messages at any time by sending the word “STOP” to 877877.  The text messaging method of entry is designed to work with most of the major wireless carriers in the United States, but Sponsor makes no guarantee that any particular wireless service provider will participate, and the mobile phone that is used must be capable of sending and receiving text messages.  Participants should check their phone’s features to see if they have that capability.  Wireless service providers may charge participants for each text message, including any error message, that is sent and received in connection with the Sweepstakes, based on the applicable wireless service pricing plan.  Participants should consult their wireless service provider’s pricing plan for details.  Proof of text messaging the Short Code is not considered proof of delivery to or receipt by Sponsor of such entry.  Entering by sending a text message will not improve your chance of winning.
<br /><br />
In the event of a dispute regarding the individual who actually submitted a text entry, the entry will be deemed submitted by the authorized account holder of the wireless account supplied at the time of entry.  The potential winner may be required to provide Sponsor with proof that he/she is the authorized account holder of the wireless account associated with the winning entry.  If a dispute cannot be resolved to Sponsor’s satisfaction, the affected entry will be deemed ineligible.  The Promotion Entities shall not be responsible for incorrect or inaccurate entry information caused by any of the equipment or programming associated with or utilized in the Sweepstakes or by any technical or human error which may occur in the processing of the entries in the Sweepstakes.  The Promotion Entities assume no responsibility or liability for any error, omission, interruption, deletion, theft or destruction, or unauthorized access to, or alteration of entries.
<br /><br />
At the end of each Weekly Period (as defined in the chart below), the School Fundraising Pages that accumulate the highest and second highest amounts of money during that given Weekly Period will be awarded a Weekly Prize.  
